OL,3,CMeet the 100-year-old driver who's
OL,4,Cbeen behind the wheel for 87 years
OL,6,F"Some people at 60 shouldn't be
OL,7,Fdriving but there again there's people
OL,8,Fat 100 that are very good drivers."
OL,10,FOther than parking on zigzags once in
OL,11,Fthe 1940s, he has had a blameless
OL,12,Frecord.
OL,14,FIn the war, he drove heavy vehicles
OL,15,Ffor the royal engineers.
OL,17,FMr Dixon's neighbour and very close
OL,18,Ffriend Margaret is often in the
OL,19,Fpassenger seat.
